The paper deals with a problem in wireless communications related to peak power reduction in multicarrier waveforms. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), communication systems (cs.COMM), signal processing (cs.SI), network infrastructure (cs.NI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Given the focus on wireless communication systems and signal processing, cs.IT and cs.COMM are the most likely sub-categories. However, the use of probability measures and iterative algorithms suggests a potential connection to cs.SI and cs.LG. Finally, the relevance to network infrastructure and wireless communication systems suggests a possible connection to cs.NI.
